<br>
New Spell Line &quot;Blasts&quot;<br>
Unresistable, highly efficient, but only a 50 foot spell range.  When you first get them they are a little overpowered, but by the time you get an upgrade, they are beginning to get left behind.<br>
<br>
M'yrddin's Blast of Magic (12) <br>
50 Damage for 5 Mana<br>
Raises caster on the Hate List by 25 (?)<br>
Resistance Check: None<br>
Cast Time: 1.5 Seconds w/ 2.5 second recovery<br>
<br>
<br>
Whitefalcon's Blast of Flame (29) <br>
175 Damage for 35 Mana<br>
Raises caster on the Hate List by 50 (?)<br>
Resistance Check: None<br>
Cast Time: 3.0 Seconds w/ 2.5 second recovery<br>
<br>
<br>
Theurgist's Blast of Light (44) <br>
400 Damage for 65 Mana<br>
Raises caster on the Hate List by 75 (?)<br>
Resistance Check: None<br>
Cast Time: 3.5 Seconds w/ 2.5 second recovery<br>
<br>
<br>
Mindspire's Blast of Ice (60)<br>
500 Damage for 80 Mana<br>
Raises caster on the Hate List by 100 (?)<br>
Resistance Check: None<br>
Cast Time: 4.0 Seconds w/ 2.5 second recovery<br>
<br>
With those cast times/ranges, it is impossible to kite with thim either with, or without snare. <br>
<br>
All Dragon-resistance mobs would be immune, possibly all giants, and any special nameds that verant decides to add this to.<br>
<br>
However, with these would come another spell:<br>
<br>
Lesser Concussion (24): Lowers you on the Hate List by 200 <br>
<br>
Now, these numbers aren't 'researched' very heavily, and could easily undergo some tweaking, but I rather like this idea as a proposal that:<br>
1) doesnt let us solo any better (these spells are ONLY usable with a tank)<br>
2) Doesn't trivialise our play (too easy to over-burn) with the &quot;just hit 'A' and walk away&quot; melee battle ease<br>
3) Gives enough range that you shouldnt have to run around and snif its tail<br>
4) Gains its power because it still lets you reserve your 'big nukes' for the end of the fight.<br>
<br>
<br>
I kind of like this idea, even though I'd rather they implement my other idea (Harvest gives 1000 mana) <p><center>
