(Aye, I've seen the comment about not &quot;researching&quot; the numbers) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=setch>Setch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/16/02 9:45:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=685.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Crazy Ideas</span><hr size=1> I always thought a neat option for harvest would be to increase the mana boost, but increase the recast time to compensate.<br>
<br>
Like, if harvest 2 did 1k but had a one hour recast time, it would be practically useless in terms of net mana regen - but it would provide a critical boost in desperate situations.<br>
<br>
Eh. Just a thought anyway. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujarnin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/18/02 5:43:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=685.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.interofficenetworks.com/demo/doh/jarninface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Crazy Ideas</span><hr size=1> Harvest = 3 mana/tick (3m/t) regen all at once at L60.<br>
<br>
If we were to get another &quot;harvest type&quot; spell, it'd likely have the same &quot;pseudo regen rate&quot;.<br>
<br>
What I'd like to see, is a mini-harvest available at level 20ish. Something like:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Gather</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Level: 20<br>
Level cost: 1<br>
Cast Time: 20 seconds<br>
Recast Time: 7.5 minutes<br>
Spell Effects: 76 (L20) to 176 (L60) mana gain, 20 second stun.<br>
Spell Discription: This spell would act like an additional 0.7 mana per tick at level 20, and 1 mana per tick at level 60. Gather has a longer cast time, and longer stun than Harvest, but is able to be recast in less time.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Reap</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Level: 53<br>
Level cost: 1<br>
Cast Time: 5 seconds<br>
Recast Time: 15 minutes<br>
Spell Effects: 523 (L53) to 601 (L60) mana gain, 5 second stun.<br>
Spell Discription: This spell would act like an additional 5 mana per tick at level 53, and 6 mana per tick at level 60. Reap has a shorter cast time, and shorter stun than Harvest, but is longer between recasts as Harvest.<br>
<br>
With these spells added in, they wouldn't overpower us, they would allow us to keep up with exp grinding, and because they take up spell slots, it's unlikely that they'd be used all together while soloing. <p><center>
