</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/20/02 11:42:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=685.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Crazy Ideas</span><hr size=1> The real problem with any damage changes in the game is that Verant is worried about what happens in the &quot;old zones&quot;, and as a result, they have been afraid to give us damage upgrades until recently.  <br>
<br>
Pre-Velious, mobs had the 32k HP limit.  Since Verant hasn't wanted to re-balance the old zones, they have left it alone.  Now, this means that any upgrades we are given to handle Velious/Luclin level mobs seems overpowered in old world/Kunark.<br>
<br>
So, what I feel Verant MUST do is to remove the old limits on the old game world, not just the high end zones, but all of them.  The risk vs. reward needs to be looked at as well on encounters, and make sure that the lower level mobs don't drop items a higher level character would want.  <br>
<br>
Vox and Naggy are the perfect example of risk vs. reward being BROKEN.  The reward is so good, (parts needed for certain epics, and other items that high level characters would want), that Verant felt they needed to restrict access to these mobs to those level 52 and below.  A better solution would be to REPLACE the mobs, change the loot table, and make it so it wouldn't be desired by the level 53-60 crowd.  Then you could remove the level limit since the loot wouldn't be the reason people hunt in places like this.<br>
<br>
I don't mean that the difficulty should be increased, simply that the 32k HP limit should be removed and so we don't see mana burn nerfed because of old world/Kunark being outmoded.<br>
 <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
Level 60 Wizard<br>
The First Seal<br>
The Nameless Server<br>
